# Ignore-rect mask for calc_fraction_sum (NumOS SDL2 emulator visual test).
#
# Reason: identical StatusBar-clock nondeterminism to calc_1_plus_2 — the only
# region that differs across separate launches is the live HH:MM clock. The label
# is drawn by StatusBar::updateClock() from the real wall clock (time() ->
# localtime -> "%02d:%02d", src/ui/StatusBar.cpp), so a golden blessed at one time
# vs a candidate generated at another differ inside the clock glyphs only. (The
# CalculationApp input cursor does NOT contribute: in --deterministic mode the
# blink phase is a function of the frame index and is byte-identical run-to-run; the
# earlier "cursor band" framing was a misdiagnosis. The empirical cross-launch diff
# is the clock.) Expected per-minute UI nondeterminism, masked in the comparator
# rather than by touching frozen renderer/cursor code.
#
# Region: the clock label is LV_ALIGN_LEFT_MID,6 in lv_font_montserrat_12
# (StatusBar.cpp:61-65), always 5 glyphs ("HH:MM"), box ~x[6..38] y[8..16]. A
# golden-vs-fresh-candidate diff put the changed pixels at x[6..37] y[8..16] (32x9).
# The previous rect 8,6,30,13 (x[8..37]) missed the clock's left edge x[6..7], which
# leaked outside the mask and FAILED CI; this rect is the shared StatusBar clock
# band used by settings_smoke / math_showcase_smoke.
#
# Rect = full HH:MM label box (~x[6..38] y[8..16]) padded ~2px on each side ->
# x[4..40] y[6..18]. Superset of the old 8,6,30,13 (no coverage regression); it
# masks only the clock — the centered title, the right-aligned battery/angle/
# modifier, and the expression/result (1/2 + 1/3 = 5/6, below the y=24 separator)
# are all outside it.
#
# x,y,w,h
4,6,37,13
